What about your brother?
What's his name?

769
01:02:54,665 --> 01:02:56,223
Timmy.

770
01:02:56,266 --> 01:02:59,030
RIPLEY:
ls Timmy around here, too?

771
01:02:59,069 --> 01:03:01,264
Maybe hiding like you were?

772
01:03:05,009 --> 01:03:06,237
Any sisters?

773
01:03:10,114 --> 01:03:11,843
Mom and Dad?

774
01:03:14,451 --> 01:03:17,750
Newt, look at me.

775
01:03:17,788 --> 01:03:18,982
Where are they?

776
01:03:19,023 --> 01:03:22,049
They're dead, all right?
Can I go now?

777
01:03:25,095 --> 01:03:26,528
I'm sorry, Newt.

778
01:03:28,065 --> 01:03:30,260
Don't you think you'd be safer
here with us?

779
01:03:34,004 --> 01:03:36,302
These people are here
to protect you.

780
01:03:36,340 --> 01:03:38,274
They're soldiers.

781
01:03:38,308 --> 01:03:41,175
It won't make any difference.

782
01:03:54,591 --> 01:03:56,752
SPUNKMEYER:
Need anything else?

783
01:03:59,229 --> 01:04:02,198
Hello, Bishop.
Do you need anything else?

784
01:04:04,401 --> 01:04:05,561
No.

785
01:04:08,205 --> 01:04:10,366
Nice pet you got there.

786
01:04:10,407 --> 01:04:13,561
Magnificent, isn't it?

787
01:04:13,694 --> 01:04:17,061
Yo! Stop your grinnin'
and drop your linen!

788
01:04:17,098 --> 01:04:18,656
Found them.

789
01:04:18,699 --> 01:04:19,927
GORMAN: They alive?

790
01:04:19,967 --> 01:04:23,266
HUDSON: Unknown, but it looks
like all of them...

791
01:04:23,304 --> 01:04:25,738
over at
the processing station...

792
01:04:25,773 --> 01:04:27,536
sub-level three...

793
01:04:27,575 --> 01:04:30,043
under the main cooling towers.

794
01:04:30,077 --> 01:04:33,911
HICKS: lt looks like
a goddamn town meeting.

795
01:04:33,948 --> 01:04:35,643
Let's saddle up, Apone.

796
01:04:35,683 --> 01:04:37,014
APONE: Aye, sir.

797
01:04:38,185 --> 01:04:43,145
Let's go. They ain't payin' us
by the hour. Head 'em out.

798
01:04:43,190 --> 01:04:45,055
OK, Frost, you're driving.

799
01:04:56,871 --> 01:05:00,272
It's OK. Don't worry.
It'll be OK.

800
01:05:40,548 --> 01:05:42,948
GORMAN: I want
a straight "V" deployment...

801
01:05:42,983 --> 01:05:45,144
second team on left flank.

802
01:05:45,186 --> 01:05:47,416
Advance on axial six-six-four.

803
01:05:47,454 --> 01:05:52,084
Tracker on-line. Set the V-gain
to filter R-F ambient.

804
01:05:52,126 --> 01:05:55,892
APONE: Hudson, tracker on-line.
Left and right, little buddy.

805
01:05:57,064 --> 01:05:59,532
GORMAN: Forty meters in,
bearing two-two-one...

806
01:05:59,567 --> 01:06:01,933
there should be a stairwell.

807
01:06:01,969 --> 01:06:03,266
APONE: Check. Got it.

808
01:06:05,206 --> 01:06:07,265
GORMAN:
You want sub-level three.

809
01:06:09,276 --> 01:06:10,538
APONE: Let's go, people.

810
01:06:10,578 --> 01:06:12,205
Hudson, you got the point.

811
01:06:12,246 --> 01:06:14,043
Hicks, watch our tails.

812
01:06:14,081 --> 01:06:16,049
Nice and easy.

813
01:06:16,083 --> 01:06:17,414
Check those corners.

814
01:06:17,451 --> 01:06:19,442
Check those corners.

815
01:06:23,057 --> 01:06:24,752
GORMAN: Watch your spacing.

816
01:06:24,792 --> 01:06:27,693
APONE: You heard the man.
Don't bunch up. Stay loose.

817
01:06:27,728 --> 01:06:30,663
GORMAN: Your transmission's
showing a lot of break-up.

818
01:06:30,698 --> 01:06:33,394
HUDSON: Probably getting some
interference from the structure.

819
01:06:33,434 --> 01:06:34,924
APONE: Use those lights.

820
01:06:37,071 --> 01:06:41,701
GORMAN: Next one down,
and proceed on a two-one-six.

821
01:06:41,742 --> 01:06:43,767
APONE: Roger.
That's a two-one-six.

822
01:06:46,046 --> 01:06:47,604
GORMAN: I'm not
making that out too well.

823
01:06:47,648 --> 01:06:49,513
What is it, Hudson?

824
01:06:49,550 --> 01:06:52,212
HUDSON:
You tell me. I only work here.

825
01:07:07,167 --> 01:07:09,294
What is that?

826
01:07:09,336 --> 01:07:11,566
I don't know.

827
01:07:12,907 --> 01:07:14,534
Proceed inside.

828
01:07:31,025 --> 01:07:33,994
APONE: Watch your fire
and check your targets.

829
01:07:34,028 --> 01:07:36,519
Remember, we're looking
for civvies in here.

830
01:07:46,407 --> 01:07:48,034
APONE: Easy.

831
01:07:48,075 --> 01:07:51,044
HICKS: Tighten it up, Frost.
We're getting a little thin.

832
01:07:52,680 --> 01:07:54,409
APONE: Nice and easy.

833
01:07:57,051 --> 01:07:59,246
DIETRICH: Looks like
some sort of secreted resin.

834
01:07:59,286 --> 01:08:03,120
HICKS:
Yeah, but secreted from what?

835
01:08:03,157 --> 01:08:05,887
APONE: Nobody touch nothing.

836
01:08:05,926 --> 01:08:08,952
BURKE:
Busy little creatures, huh?

837
01:08:08,996 --> 01:08:11,260
FROST: Hot as hell in here.

838
01:08:11,298 --> 01:08:13,027
HUDSON: But it's a dry heat.

839
01:08:13,067 --> 01:08:14,728
APONE: Knock it off, Hudson.

840
01:08:23,177 --> 01:08:26,169
Lieutenant,
what do those pulse-rifles fire?

841
01:08:26,213 --> 01:08:29,046
GORMAN: Ten millimeter
explosive-tip caseless.

842
01:08:29,083 --> 01:08:31,176
Standard light
armor-piercing round. Why?

843
01:08:31,218 --> 01:08:33,379
RIPLEY: Look where your team is.

844
01:08:33,420 --> 01:08:36,583
They're right under
the primary heat exchangers.

845
01:08:36,623 --> 01:08:37,783
So?

846
01:08:37,825 --> 01:08:41,352
So if they fire their weapons
in there...

847
01:08:41,395 --> 01:08:42,623
won't they rupture
the cooling system?

848
01:08:42,663 --> 01:08:45,689
BURKE: Oh, ho ho. Yeah.
She's absolutely right.

849
01:08:45,733 --> 01:08:46,995
So what?

850
01:08:47,034 --> 01:08:51,266
This whole station is basically
a big fusion reactor.

851
01:08:52,506 --> 01:08:53,734
Right?

852
01:08:53,774 --> 01:08:56,709
So she's talking about
a thermonuclear explosion...

853
01:08:56,744 --> 01:08:58,473
and, "Adiós, muchachos."

854
01:08:58,512 --> 01:09:01,174
Oh, great. Wonderful.

855
01:09:01,215 --> 01:09:03,740
Shit!

856
01:09:05,753 --> 01:09:07,220
Look.

857
01:09:07,254 --> 01:09:09,848
Uh... Apone.

858
01:09:11,191 --> 01:09:14,752
We can't have any firing
in there.

859
01:09:14,795 --> 01:09:18,424
I want you to collect
magazines from everybody.

860
01:09:18,465 --> 01:09:19,955
HUDSON: ls he fuckin' crazy?

861
01:09:20,000 --> 01:09:22,594
FROST:
What do we use, harsh language?

862
01:09:22,636 --> 01:09:24,570
GORMAN: Flame units only.
I want rifles slung.

863
01:09:24,605 --> 01:09:25,765
APONE: Sir, I...

864
01:09:25,806 --> 01:09:28,536
GORMAN: Just do it, Sergeant.
And no grenades.

865
01:09:30,210 --> 01:09:32,007
APONE: You heard the man.

866
01:09:32,046 --> 01:09:34,276
Pull 'em out. Let's have 'em.

867
01:09:35,315 --> 01:09:37,715
Come on, Vasquez.
Clear and lock.

868
01:09:41,221 --> 01:09:42,381
Damn!

869
01:09:43,257 --> 01:09:45,418
You, too. Give it up, Ski.

870
01:09:45,459 --> 01:09:48,451
Crowe, I want it now.
Give it up.

871
01:09:48,495 --> 01:09:49,928
DRAKE: Right on, Vas.

872
01:09:51,765 --> 01:09:53,699
APONE: Let's go. Give it up.

873
01:09:53,734 --> 01:09:55,895
Frost, you got the duty.
Open that bag.

874
01:09:55,936 --> 01:09:57,494
FROST: Thanks a lot, Sarge.

875
01:09:57,538 --> 01:09:58,937
APONE: Hicks, cover our ass.

876
01:09:58,972 --> 01:10:00,803
Head 'em out, people.

877
01:10:02,743 --> 01:10:06,702
HICKS: I like to keep this handy
for close encounters.

878
01:10:06,747 --> 01:10:08,544
FROST: I heard that.

879
01:10:17,591 --> 01:10:19,354
GORMAN: Any movement?

880
01:10:19,393 --> 01:10:20,883
HUDSON: Nothing.

881
01:10:20,928 --> 01:10:22,122
Zip.

882
01:10:34,708 --> 01:10:37,541
APONE: Holy shit.

883
01:10:50,224 --> 01:10:52,590
RIPLEY: Newt, go sit up front.

884
01:10:52,626 --> 01:10:53,957
Go on!

885
01:10:53,994 --> 01:10:55,222
Now!

886
01:11:23,720 --> 01:11:26,518
APONE: Steady, people.
Let's finish our sweep.

887
01:11:26,556 --> 01:11:29,923
We're still Marines,
and we got a job to do.

888
01:11:29,960 --> 01:11:31,450
Keep it moving.

889
01:11:32,462 --> 01:11:33,827
Easy.

890
01:12:05,929 --> 01:12:07,453
- Top!
- What?

891
01:12:07,497 --> 01:12:09,192
DIETRICH: We got a live one!

892
01:12:09,232 --> 01:12:10,699
You're gonna be all right.

893
01:12:10,734 --> 01:12:13,567
Please... kill me.

894
01:12:13,603 --> 01:12:15,503
DIETRICH:
Stay calm. We'll get you out.

895
01:12:15,539 --> 01:12:17,734
It's gonna be all right.

896
01:12:17,774 --> 01:12:19,469
We've got to get her
out of here.

897
01:12:19,509 --> 01:12:20,771
APONE: What is it, Dietrich?
What's going on?

898
01:12:20,811 --> 01:12:22,301
Convulsion!

899
01:12:22,345 --> 01:12:23,505
RIPLEY: Ohh!

900
01:12:23,547 --> 01:12:25,777
APONE: Dietrich, get back!

901
01:12:25,816 --> 01:12:27,545
Aah! Aah!

902
01:12:33,890 --> 01:12:35,255
No!

903
01:12:35,292 --> 01:12:37,351
APONE: Frost, flamethrower!

904
01:12:37,394 --> 01:12:39,954
Get back! Flamethrower! Move!

905
01:12:39,996 --> 01:12:41,156
[Screeching]

906
01:13:09,759 --> 01:13:11,522
- [Beeping]
- Movement!

907
01:13:11,561 --> 01:13:12,721
What's the position?

908
01:13:14,264 --> 01:13:16,459
I can't lock in!

909
01:13:16,499 --> 01:13:18,831
Talk to me, Hudson!

910
01:13:18,869 --> 01:13:21,337
Multiple signals.

911
01:13:21,371 --> 01:13:22,998
They're closing.

912
01:13:24,341 --> 01:13:27,674
APONE: Go to infrared, people.
Look sharp!

913
01:13:27,711 --> 01:13:30,976
GORMAN: What's happening, Apone?
We can't see anything in here.

914
01:13:31,014 --> 01:13:33,073
RIPLEY:
Pull your team out, Gorman.

915
01:13:38,889 --> 01:13:41,687
HUDSON: I got readings
in front and behind.

916
01:13:41,725 --> 01:13:44,091
FROST: Where, man?
I don't see shit.

917
01:13:44,127 --> 01:13:46,561
HICKS: He's right.
Nothing's back here.

918
01:13:46,596 --> 01:13:49,064
HUDSON: Something's moving,
and it ain't us!

919
01:13:50,567 --> 01:13:52,057
FROST: Oh, shit.

920
01:13:52,102 --> 01:13:54,002
HUDSON:
Tracker's off-scale, man.

921
01:13:54,037 --> 01:13:57,336
They're all around us, man!
Jesus!

922
01:13:57,374 --> 01:14:00,707
DIETRICH: Maybe they don't
show up on infrared at all.

923
01:14:04,748 --> 01:14:06,215
Aah!

924
01:14:07,951 --> 01:14:09,179
FROST: Aah!

925
01:14:10,553 --> 01:14:11,679
APONE: Frost!

926
01:14:11,721 --> 01:14:13,188
DIETRICH: Aah!

927
01:14:17,460 --> 01:14:19,394
Come on!

928
01:14:23,767 --> 01:14:25,735
CROWE: Aah!

929
01:14:25,769 --> 01:14:28,363
GORMAN: Jesus Christ, Apone!
What is going on?

930
01:14:28,405 --> 01:14:30,669
HICKS: Wierzbowski
and Crowe are down!

931
01:14:30,707 --> 01:14:34,803
APONE:
Dietrich, Crowe! Sound off!

932
01:14:34,844 --> 01:14:37,608
Frost! Frost!

933
01:14:39,816 --> 01:14:41,306
WIERZBOWSKl: Aah!

934
01:14:41,351 --> 01:14:43,444
Wierzbowski!

935
01:14:43,486 --> 01:14:44,714
Wierzbowski!

936
01:14:44,754 --> 01:14:46,312
WIERZBOWSKl: Aah!

937
01:14:46,356 --> 01:14:48,290
VASQUEZ: Let's rock!

938
01:14:48,325 --> 01:14:49,986
DRAKE: Yeah!

939
01:14:50,026 --> 01:14:52,756
Yeah!

940
01:14:52,796 --> 01:14:54,286
Who's firing? God damn it!

941
01:14:55,298 --> 01:14:56,629
VASQUEZ: Yeah!

942
01:14:56,666 --> 01:14:58,190
I ordered a hold fire.

943
01:14:59,035 --> 01:15:03,165
HUDSON: They're coming out of
the goddamn walls! Let's book!

944
01:15:03,206 --> 01:15:05,231
Uh, Apone...

945
01:15:05,275 --> 01:15:08,301
I want you to lay down
a suppressing fire with...

946
01:15:08,345 --> 01:15:11,280
APONE: Vasquez, Drake,
hold your fire, God damn it!

947
01:15:11,314 --> 01:15:13,214
GORMAN: Are you copying me?

948
01:15:13,249 --> 01:15:15,547
Lay down a suppressing fire
with the incinerators...

949
01:15:15,585 --> 01:15:17,018
and fall back by squads...

950
01:15:17,053 --> 01:15:18,350
APONE: Say again?

951
01:15:18,388 --> 01:15:20,253
All after "incinerator."

952
01:15:20,290 --> 01:15:24,317
Lay down a suppressing fire
with the incinerators...

953
01:15:24,361 --> 01:15:25,726
and fall back...

954
01:15:25,762 --> 01:15:27,627
[Loud gunfire]

955
01:15:29,632 --> 01:15:31,497
APONE: Aah!

956
01:15:31,534 --> 01:15:32,660
HUDSON: Sarge!

957
01:15:32,702 --> 01:15:35,967
Apone, talk to me.

958
01:15:36,006 --> 01:15:37,633
Apone? Talk to me!

959
01:15:37,674 --> 01:15:38,834
RIPLEY: He's gone!

960
01:15:38,875 --> 01:15:40,467
[Shouting and gunfire]

961
01:15:40,510 --> 01:15:42,978
Get them out of there!

962
01:15:43,013 --> 01:15:44,776
GORMAN: Shut up!

963
01:15:44,814 --> 01:15:46,577
Hicks, whoever's left,
get the hell...

964
01:15:46,616 --> 01:15:47,981
- Shut up!
- God damn it!

965
01:15:49,753 --> 01:15:51,345
HICKS: Where's Apone?!

966
01:15:51,388 --> 01:15:52,514
Where's Apone?!

967
01:15:52,555 --> 01:15:55,991
The Sarge is gone!
Let's get the fuck out of here!

968
01:15:56,026 --> 01:15:57,653
HICKS: Let's go, Marines!

969
01:15:58,762 --> 01:16:00,286
Hudson?

970
01:16:00,330 --> 01:16:01,957
Vasquez?

971
01:16:01,998 --> 01:16:03,795
HICKS: Hudson, look out!

972
01:16:03,833 --> 01:16:05,130
HUDSON: Get it!

973
01:16:06,269 --> 01:16:07,759
HICKS: Hudson!

974
01:16:07,804 --> 01:16:09,237
GORMAN: Hicks! Hicks!

975
01:16:09,272 --> 01:16:11,001
HICKS: lt's too much!
Fall back!

976
01:16:11,041 --> 01:16:13,134
GORMAN:
I told them to fall back.

977
01:16:13,176 --> 01:16:14,336
I told them to fall back.

978
01:16:14,377 --> 01:16:16,402
RIPLEY: They're cut off!

979
01:16:16,446 --> 01:16:18,505
Do something!

980
01:16:18,548 --> 01:16:20,311
Fuck!

981
01:16:20,350 --> 01:16:21,510
HICKS: Keep movin'!

982
01:16:21,551 --> 01:16:23,416
RIPLEY: Hold on, Newt.

983
01:16:29,726 --> 01:16:32,354
Ripley,
what the hell are you doing?

984
01:16:38,334 --> 01:16:39,961
GORMAN: Turn around!

985
01:16:43,440 --> 01:16:44,839
That's an order!

986
01:16:49,312 --> 01:16:51,280
RIPLEY: Get off me, damn it!

987
01:16:51,314 --> 01:16:52,838
GORMAN:
God damn it, that's an order!

988
01:16:52,882 --> 01:16:54,543
BURKE:
You had your chance, Gorman.

989
01:17:06,830 --> 01:17:08,297
HICKS: Come on!

990
01:17:08,331 --> 01:17:09,798
VASQUEZ: Come on, Drake!

991
01:17:26,516 --> 01:17:28,347
DRAKE: Yeah!

992
01:17:28,384 --> 01:17:29,942
HICKS: Let's move it!

993
01:17:31,020 --> 01:17:33,488
VASQUEZ:
Come on. Let's go! Let's go!

994
01:17:33,523 --> 01:17:37,050
HUDSON: lt's blocked, man.
We got to go around!

995
01:17:37,093 --> 01:17:38,754
RIPLEY: Open the door! Hicks!

996
01:17:38,795 --> 01:17:41,389
HICKS: Drake, we are leaving!

997
01:17:44,834 --> 01:17:46,563
DRAKE: Run for it!

998
01:17:48,505 --> 01:17:49,699
Shit!

999
01:17:53,710 --> 01:17:55,302
[Grunting]

1000
01:17:55,345 --> 01:17:56,471
BURKE: Let's go!

1001
01:17:56,513 --> 01:17:58,174
VASQUEZ: Drake, come on, man!

1002
01:18:05,054 --> 01:18:06,282
Drake, come on!

1003
01:18:10,026 --> 01:18:12,187
Aah!

1004
01:18:12,228 --> 01:18:13,718
No!

1005
01:18:15,798 --> 01:18:17,642
HUDSON: Fire in the hold!

1006
01:18:17,775 --> 01:18:18,935
HICKS: He's gone!

1007
01:18:18,976 --> 01:18:20,534
VASQUEZ: No! Drake's out there!

1008
01:18:20,578 --> 01:18:22,205
HUDSON: Put it out!

1009
01:18:22,246 --> 01:18:23,941
VASQUEZ: Drake's coming!

1010
01:18:23,981 --> 01:18:25,846
HICKS: He's gone!

1011
01:18:25,883 --> 01:18:27,373
VASQUEZ: No, he's not!

1012
01:18:28,820 --> 01:18:30,788
HICKS: Forget him! He's gone!

1013
01:18:36,093 --> 01:18:38,425
Get on the goddamn door!

1014
01:18:41,165 --> 01:18:42,962
HICKS: Eat this!

1015
01:18:44,702 --> 01:18:46,693
HUDSON: Aah!

1016
01:18:46,737 --> 01:18:50,229
HICKS: Ripley! Go, go, go!

1017
01:19:00,218 --> 01:19:01,981
HICKS: Whoa!

1018
01:19:13,297 --> 01:19:14,457
GORMAN: Oh.

1019
01:19:23,574 --> 01:19:25,166
[Screeches]

1020
01:19:34,652 --> 01:19:36,552
[Screeches]

1021
01:19:52,937 --> 01:19:54,905
HICKS:
lt's all right! We're clear!

1022
01:19:54,939 --> 01:19:57,908
Ripley,
you've blown the transaxle!

1023
01:19:57,942 --> 01:19:59,910
You're just grinding metal!

1024
01:19:59,944 --> 01:20:02,037
Come on, ease down.

1025
01:20:02,079 --> 01:20:03,910
Ease down.

1026
01:20:03,948 --> 01:20:05,108
Ease down.

1027
01:20:06,350 --> 01:20:07,749
Ease down.

1028
01:20:19,363 --> 01:20:20,694
RIPLEY: You OK?

1029
01:20:22,500 --> 01:20:24,491
HUDSON: I'm all right.

1030
01:20:24,535 --> 01:20:27,663
Get away from me, man!

1031
01:20:27,705 --> 01:20:29,138
HICKS: Lieutenant.

1032
01:20:29,173 --> 01:20:31,573
RIPLEY: What happened to Gorman?

1033
01:20:31,609 --> 01:20:32,871
HICKS: I don't know...

1034
01:20:32,910 --> 01:20:35,174
maybe a concussion,
but he's alive.

1035
01:20:35,212 --> 01:20:37,077
VASQUEZ: No, man, he's dead!

1036
01:20:37,114 --> 01:20:39,378
Wake up, pendejo!
I'm going to kill you!

1037
01:20:39,417 --> 01:20:40,884
HICKS: Back off.

1038
01:20:40,918 --> 01:20:42,408
Right now.

1039
01:20:44,922 --> 01:20:47,220
Somebody get me a first aid kit.

1040
01:20:47,258 --> 01:20:50,386
HUDSON: Hey. Hey, look.

1041
01:20:50,428 --> 01:20:52,896
The Sarge and Dietrich
aren't dead, man.

1042
01:20:52,930 --> 01:20:55,865
Their signs are real low,
but they ain't dead.

1043
01:20:55,900 --> 01:20:57,299
Then we get them.

1044
01:20:57,335 --> 01:20:59,599
- We don't leave people behind!
- I ain't going back!

1045
01:20:59,637 --> 01:21:01,605
You can't help them!

1046
01:21:03,274 --> 01:21:04,764
You can't.

1047
01:21:04,809 --> 01:21:07,937
Right now they're being cocooned
just like the others.

1048
01:21:11,649 --> 01:21:14,413
HUDSON: Oh, dear Lord Jesus,
this ain't happenin', man.

1049
01:21:14,452 --> 01:21:15,919
HICKS: God damn it.

1050
01:21:15,953 --> 01:21:18,421
HUDSON:
This can't be happenin', man.

1051
01:21:18,456 --> 01:21:19,684
This isn't happenin'!

1052
01:21:19,824 --> 01:21:22,918
We've got
seven canisters of CN-20.

1053
01:21:22,960 --> 01:21:26,896
I say we roll them in there
and nerve gas the whole nest.

1054
01:21:26,931 --> 01:21:29,900
HICKS: lt's worth a try, but we
don't know if it'll affect them.

1055
01:21:29,934 --> 01:21:34,064
HUDSON: Let's bug out and call
it even. Why even talk about it?

1056
01:21:34,105 --> 01:21:37,905
RIPLEY: I say we take off and
nuke the entire site from orbit.

1057
01:21:40,911 --> 01:21:42,742
It's the only way to be sure.

1058
01:21:42,780 --> 01:21:44,372
HUDSON: Fuckin' "A"!

1059
01:21:44,415 --> 01:21:46,110
BURKE: Hold on one second.

1060
01:21:46,150 --> 01:21:50,348
This installation
has a substantial dollar value.

1061
01:21:50,388 --> 01:21:51,787
They can bill me.

1062
01:21:53,190 --> 01:21:54,384
OK, look.

1063
01:21:54,425 --> 01:21:57,883
This is an emotional moment
for all of us, OK?

1064
01:21:57,928 --> 01:21:59,054
I know that.

1065
01:21:59,096 --> 01:22:01,894
But let's not make
snap judgments, please.

1066
01:22:01,932 --> 01:22:04,992
This is clearly an important
species we're dealing with...

1067
01:22:05,036 --> 01:22:07,800
and I don't think you or I
or anybody has the right...

1068
01:22:07,838 --> 01:22:09,396
to arbitrarily exterminate them.

1069
01:22:09,440 --> 01:22:10,600
Wrong.

1070
01:22:10,641 --> 01:22:12,268
VASQUEZ: Yeah. Watch us.

1071
01:22:12,309 --> 01:22:14,834
HUDSON: Maybe you haven't been
keeping up on current events...

1072
01:22:14,879 --> 01:22:17,370
but we just got
our asses kicked, pal!

1073
01:22:17,415 --> 01:22:20,907
I'm not blind
to what's going on...

1074
01:22:20,951 --> 01:22:24,614
but I cannot authorize that kind
of action. I'm sorry.

1075
01:22:26,524 --> 01:22:31,723
Well, I believe Corporal Hicks
has authority here.

1076
01:22:33,531 --> 01:22:34,998
Corporal Hicks is...

1077
01:22:35,032 --> 01:22:37,728
RIPLEY: This operation
is under military jurisdiction.

1078
01:22:37,768 --> 01:22:40,999
Hicks is next in chain
of command, right, Corporal?

1079
01:22:42,373 --> 01:22:43,533
Yeah.

1080
01:22:45,042 --> 01:22:46,566
Yeah, that's right.

1081
01:22:47,678 --> 01:22:49,612
BURKE: Yeah. Look, Ripley...

1082
01:22:49,647 --> 01:22:51,945
this is a multimillion dollar
installation, OK?

1083
01:22:51,982 --> 01:22:55,543
He can't make that decision.
He's just a grunt.

1084
01:22:55,586 --> 01:22:56,985
Uh, no offense.

1085
01:22:57,021 --> 01:22:58,454
HICKS: None taken.

1086
01:22:58,489 --> 01:22:59,956
Ferro, do you copy?

1087
01:22:59,990 --> 01:23:01,116
FERRO: Standing by.

1088
01:23:01,158 --> 01:23:03,558
HICKS: Prep for dust-off.
We need immediate evac.

1089
01:23:03,594 --> 01:23:05,459
FERRO: Roger. On our way.

1090
01:23:05,496 --> 01:23:08,624
HICKS: I say we take off,
nuke the site from orbit.

1091
01:23:08,666 --> 01:23:10,258
It's the only way to be sure.

1092
01:23:12,870 --> 01:23:14,633
Let's do it.

1093
01:23:21,612 --> 01:23:23,739
HICKS: Let's go.
Pick it up, Hudson.

1094
01:23:23,781 --> 01:23:25,510
Pick it up, baby.

1095
01:23:30,221 --> 01:23:32,712
All right. Set him down here.

1096
01:23:39,263 --> 01:23:41,288
Move it, Spunkmeyer.
We're rolling.

1097
01:23:46,237 --> 01:23:48,865
Hold on a second.
There's something...

1098
01:23:48,906 --> 01:23:50,874
FERRO: Just get up here.

1099
01:23:50,908 --> 01:23:53,342
I'm in. Ramp closing.

1100
01:24:13,109 --> 01:24:15,669
Spunkmeyer.

1101
01:24:15,712 --> 01:24:17,407
God damn it.

1102
01:24:17,447 --> 01:24:18,937
[Door slides open]

1103
01:24:20,216 --> 01:24:22,275
Well, where the fuck...

1104
01:24:34,998 --> 01:24:36,226
Run!

1105
01:25:17,874 --> 01:25:21,173
Well, that's great.
That's just fuckin' great, man.

1106
01:25:21,211 --> 01:25:24,237
Now what the fuck
are we supposed to do?

1107
01:25:24,280 --> 01:25:26,680
We're in some real
pretty shit now, man!

1108
01:25:26,716 --> 01:25:27,876
HICKS: Are you finished?

1109
01:25:31,754 --> 01:25:33,415
HICKS: You all right?

1110
01:25:38,661 --> 01:25:43,189
NEWT: I guess we're not
gonna be leaving now, right?

1111
01:25:43,233 --> 01:25:44,530
RIPLEY: I'm sorry, Newt.

1112
01:25:44,567 --> 01:25:48,128
You don't have to be sorry.
It wasn't your fault.

1113
01:25:48,171 --> 01:25:50,639
HUDSON: That's it, man.
Game over, man! Game over!

1114
01:25:50,673 --> 01:25:52,868
What the fuck
are we gonna do now?

1115
01:25:52,909 --> 01:25:54,376
What are we gonna do?

1116
01:25:54,410 --> 01:25:57,379
BURKE: Maybe we could build
a fire, sing a couple of songs.

1117
01:25:57,413 --> 01:25:58,880
Why don't we try that?

1118
01:25:58,915 --> 01:26:01,713
NEWT: We'd better get back
'cause it'll be dark soon...

1119
01:26:01,751 --> 01:26:03,378
and they mostly come at night.

1120
01:26:03,419 --> 01:26:04,750
Mostly.

1121
01:26:21,704 --> 01:26:22,932
HICKS: That's everything, right?

1122
01:26:23,873 --> 01:26:26,103
This is absolutely everything
we could salvage...

1123
01:26:26,142 --> 01:26:28,610
out of the APC wreckage.

1124
01:26:28,645 --> 01:26:32,604
We got four pulse-rifles
with about fifty rounds each.

1125
01:26:32,649 --> 01:26:34,617
That ain't so good.

1126
01:26:34,651 --> 01:26:38,109
We got fifteen
of these M-40 grenades.

1127
01:26:38,154 --> 01:26:41,646
Don't touch that.
Dangerous, honey.

1128
01:26:41,691 --> 01:26:43,090
RIPLEY:
ls that the only flamethrower?

1129
01:26:43,693 --> 01:26:47,220
HICKS: Yeah. It's only
half-full, but it's functional.

1130
01:26:47,263 --> 01:26:48,855
And another one's damaged.

1131
01:26:48,898 --> 01:26:51,059
I don't know about that one.

1132
01:26:51,100 --> 01:26:53,364
But the good news...

1133
01:26:53,403 --> 01:26:55,963
we got four of these
robot sentries...

1134
01:26:56,973 --> 01:27:00,067
with display
and scanners intact.

1135
01:27:00,109 --> 01:27:03,078
They really kick ass.
They'll come in handy.

1136
01:27:03,112 --> 01:27:06,775
How long after we're declared
overdue can we expect a rescue?

1137
01:27:09,819 --> 01:27:12,014
Seventeen days.

1138
01:27:12,055 --> 01:27:14,387
Seventeen days?

1139
01:27:14,424 --> 01:27:17,393
Hey, man, I don't wanna
rain on your parade...

1140
01:27:17,427 --> 01:27:19,520
but we're not gonna last
seventeen hours.

1141
01:27:19,562 --> 01:27:23,259
Those things are gonna come here
like they did before, and...

1142
01:27:23,299 --> 01:27:25,494
Hudson! Hudson!

1143
01:27:26,469 --> 01:27:28,835
This little girl
survived longer than that...

1144
01:27:28,871 --> 01:27:31,237
with no weapons and no training.

1145
01:27:31,274 --> 01:27:32,673
Right?

1146
01:27:36,012 --> 01:27:38,139
Why don't you put her in charge?

1147
01:27:38,181 --> 01:27:39,944
You better just start
dealing with it, Hudson.

1148
01:27:39,983 --> 01:27:43,942
Deal with it,
because we need you...

1149
01:27:43,987 --> 01:27:46,012
and I'm sick of your bullshit.

1150
01:27:46,055 --> 01:27:50,617
Now get on a terminal
and call up a floor plan file.

1151
01:27:50,660 --> 01:27:52,491
Construction blueprints.
I don't care.

1152
01:27:52,528 --> 01:27:54,155
Anything that shows the layout.

1153
01:27:54,197 --> 01:27:56,461
- Are you listening?
- Yeah.

1154
01:27:56,499 --> 01:27:59,866
RIPLEY: I need to see air ducts,
electrical access tunnels...

1155
01:27:59,902 --> 01:28:01,494
sub-basements...

1156
01:28:01,537 --> 01:28:03,903
every possible way
into this complex.

1157
01:28:05,341 --> 01:28:07,241
We don't have much time.

1158
01:28:07,276 --> 01:28:08,641
OK.

1159
01:28:09,779 --> 01:28:11,076
OK, I'm on it.

1160
01:28:11,114 --> 01:28:12,274
RIPLEY: Hudson!

1161
01:28:12,315 --> 01:28:14,044
Just relax.

1162
01:28:20,523 --> 01:28:21,956
l'll be in med lab.

1163
01:28:22,525 --> 01:28:25,494
l'll check on Gorman,
continue my analysis.

1164
01:28:25,528 --> 01:28:26,927
Fine.

1165
01:28:26,963 --> 01:28:28,794
You do that.

1166
01:28:34,670 --> 01:28:35,967
RIPLEY: This service tunnel...

1167
01:28:36,005 --> 01:28:38,530
must be how
they're moving back and forth.

1168
01:28:38,574 --> 01:28:39,700
HUDSON: That's right.

1169
01:28:39,742 --> 01:28:41,209
It moves from
the processing station...

1170
01:28:41,244 --> 01:28:43,712
right into the sub-level.

1171
01:28:45,381 --> 01:28:46,780
Come down on that.

1172
01:28:46,816 --> 01:28:49,011
OK, come over.

1173
01:28:49,052 --> 01:28:50,519
Hold it. Go back.

1174
01:28:50,553 --> 01:28:52,043
Punch that in there.

1175
01:28:57,093 --> 01:28:58,754
HICKS: No. It's back here.

1176
01:28:58,795 --> 01:28:59,955
RIPLEY: OK.

1177
01:29:01,431 --> 01:29:04,161
There's a pressure door
at this end.

1178
01:29:04,200 --> 01:29:07,863
Couldn't we put a remote
sentry unit in the tunnel...

1179
01:29:07,904 --> 01:29:09,201
then seal that door?

1180
01:29:09,238 --> 01:29:10,432
HICKS: That'll work...

1181
01:29:10,473 --> 01:29:12,873
but we gotta figure on them
getting into the complex.

1182
01:29:12,909 --> 01:29:14,137
RIPLEY: That's right, so...

1183
01:29:14,177 --> 01:29:16,873
we repair the barricades
at these two intersections...

1184
01:29:16,913 --> 01:29:18,073
HICKS: Right.

1185
01:29:18,114 --> 01:29:21,880
...and weld plate steel over
these ducts here and here...

1186
01:29:21,918 --> 01:29:23,681
and here.

1187
01:29:23,719 --> 01:29:27,314
Then they can only come at us
from these two corridors.

1188
01:29:27,356 --> 01:29:31,417
HICKS: Right. Then we put
the other sentry units here...

1189
01:29:31,461 --> 01:29:33,156
and here, right?

1190
01:29:33,196 --> 01:29:34,823
- Right.
- Outstanding.

1191
01:29:34,864 --> 01:29:37,765
Now all we need
is a deck of cards.

1192
01:29:39,869 --> 01:29:42,201
Let's move
like we've got a purpose.

1193
01:29:42,238 --> 01:29:43,705
HUDSON: Affirmative.

1194
01:29:43,739 --> 01:29:45,229
NEWT: Affirmative.

1195
01:30:00,256 --> 01:30:02,087
HUDSON: Do your thing, baby.

1196
01:30:02,125 --> 01:30:04,685
Come on, Vasquez,
let's get out of here.

1197
01:30:04,727 --> 01:30:07,093
"A" and "B" sentries
are in place and keyed.

1198
01:30:07,130 --> 01:30:10,327
HICKS: Roger.
Stand by. Arming now.

1199
01:30:10,366 --> 01:30:11,890
Test it, Hudson.

1200
01:30:11,934 --> 01:30:14,334
- Do it.
- Fire in the hole!

1201
01:30:17,907 --> 01:30:20,603
HUDSON: Great.
Let's get the hell out of here.

1202
01:30:20,643 --> 01:30:22,440
We're sealing the tunnel.

1203
01:30:22,478 --> 01:30:23,877
Come on, baby.

1204
01:30:35,858 --> 01:30:37,519
HICKS: For what it's worth.

1205
01:30:39,862 --> 01:30:42,228
I want you to put this on.

1206
01:30:43,366 --> 01:30:44,594
RIPLEY: What's it for?

1207
01:30:44,634 --> 01:30:45,828
It's a locator.

1208
01:30:45,868 --> 01:30:49,463
Then I can find you anywhere
in the complex on this.

1209
01:30:50,873 --> 01:30:52,864
It's just a precaution.

1210
01:30:53,876 --> 01:30:55,343
Thanks.

1211
01:30:55,378 --> 01:30:58,347
Doesn't mean we're engaged
or anything.

1212
01:30:58,381 --> 01:31:00,313
All right, what's next?

1213
01:31:29,609 --> 01:31:31,099
RIPLEY: Last stop.

1214
01:31:35,615 --> 01:31:37,082
Get in.

1215
01:31:37,116 --> 01:31:39,107
Scoot down.

1216
01:31:40,620 --> 01:31:42,087
That's good.

1217
01:31:42,121 --> 01:31:44,681
Now lie here and have a nap.

1218
01:31:44,724 --> 01:31:46,191
You're very tired.

1219
01:31:46,225 --> 01:31:49,592
I don't want to.
I have scary dreams.

1220
01:31:51,831 --> 01:31:55,198
Well, I bet Casey
doesn't have scary dreams.

1221
01:31:55,234 --> 01:31:57,202
Let's take a look.

1222
01:31:57,236 --> 01:31:59,568
Nope. Nothing bad in there.

1223
01:31:59,605 --> 01:32:00,867
See?

1224
01:32:00,907 --> 01:32:03,307
Maybe you could just
try to be like her.

1225
01:32:03,342 --> 01:32:06,709
Ripley, she doesn't
have bad dreams...

1226
01:32:06,746 --> 01:32:09,681
because she's just
a piece of plastic.

1227
01:32:09,715 --> 01:32:11,410
Right.

1228
01:32:11,450 --> 01:32:13,441
I'm sorry, Newt.

1229
01:32:19,926 --> 01:32:21,587
RIPLEY: There.

1230
01:32:21,627 --> 01:32:25,154
My mommy always said
there were no monsters...

1231
01:32:25,198 --> 01:32:28,565
no real ones, but there are.

1232
01:32:28,601 --> 01:32:31,832
Yes, there are, aren't there?

1233
01:32:33,706 --> 01:32:36,300
Why do they tell
little kids that?

1234
01:32:38,377 --> 01:32:40,072
Most of the time it's true.

1235
01:32:40,112 --> 01:32:43,604
Did one of those things
grow inside her?

1236
01:32:44,617 --> 01:32:46,346
I don't know, Newt.

1237
01:32:46,385 --> 01:32:48,546
That's the truth.

1238
01:32:48,588 --> 01:32:51,022
Isn't that how babies come...

1239
01:32:51,057 --> 01:32:53,252
I mean, people babies?

1240
01:32:53,292 --> 01:32:54,850
They grow inside you.

1241
01:32:54,894 --> 01:32:56,862
No. That's very different.

1242
01:32:56,896 --> 01:32:58,864
NEWT: Did you ever have a baby?

1243
01:32:58,898 --> 01:33:00,365
Yes, I did.

1244
01:33:00,399 --> 01:33:02,333
I had a little girl.

1245
01:33:02,368 --> 01:33:04,336
Where is she?

1246
01:33:05,404 --> 01:33:06,928
She's gone.

1247
01:33:08,574 --> 01:33:10,667
You mean dead.

1248
01:33:12,144 --> 01:33:13,634
Here.

1249
01:33:15,147 --> 01:33:16,637
Take this.

1250
01:33:17,950 --> 01:33:19,645
For luck.

1251
01:33:22,922 --> 01:33:24,412
How's that?

1252
01:33:27,593 --> 01:33:29,083
Don't go, please.

1253
01:33:29,128 --> 01:33:31,494
Newt, I'm gonna be
right in the next room.

1254
01:33:33,099 --> 01:33:34,862
And you see that camera?

1255
01:33:34,900 --> 01:33:37,733
I can see you
through that camera...

1256
01:33:37,770 --> 01:33:40,034
to see if you're safe.

1257
01:33:44,477 --> 01:33:47,173
I'm not gonna leave you, Newt.

1258
01:33:47,213 --> 01:33:49,511
I mean that.

1259
01:33:49,548 --> 01:33:51,209
That's a promise.

1260
01:33:51,250 --> 01:33:52,808
You promise?

1261
01:33:54,220 --> 01:33:56,313
I cross my heart.

1262
01:33:56,355 --> 01:33:58,118
And hope to die?

1263
01:33:59,225 --> 01:34:00,692
And hope to die.

1264
01:34:14,974 --> 01:34:16,965
Now go to sleep...

1265
01:34:17,009 --> 01:34:20,069
and don't dream.

1266
01:34:23,983 --> 01:34:25,348
Sneak.

1267
01:34:34,860 --> 01:34:36,828
BISHOP:
The molecular acid oxidizes...

1268
01:34:36,862 --> 01:34:39,057
after the creature's death,
completely neutralizing it.

1269
01:34:39,098 --> 01:34:42,829
Bishop, that's interesting,
but it gets us nowhere.

1270
01:34:42,868 --> 01:34:45,336
I'm trying to figure out
what we're dealing with.

1271
01:34:45,371 --> 01:34:46,838
Let's go through it again.

1272
01:34:46,872 --> 01:34:49,841
They grab the colonists,
they move them over there...

1273
01:34:49,875 --> 01:34:53,834
and they immobilize them
to be hosts for more of these.

1274
01:34:53,879 --> 01:34:57,508
Which means there would have
to be a lot of these parasites.

1275
01:34:57,550 --> 01:35:00,383
One for each colonist.
That's over a hundred, at least.

1276
01:35:00,419 --> 01:35:02,387
Yes. That follows.

1277
01:35:02,421 --> 01:35:06,221
Each one of these things
comes from an egg, right?

1278
01:35:09,228 --> 01:35:10,991
So who's laying these eggs?

1279
01:35:12,098 --> 01:35:13,463
I'm not sure.

1280
01:35:13,499 --> 01:35:16,195
It must be something
we haven't seen yet.

1281
01:35:16,235 --> 01:35:18,533
Hey, maybe
it's like an ant hive.

1282
01:35:18,571 --> 01:35:21,870
- Bees have hives.
- You know what I mean.

1283
01:35:21,907 --> 01:35:24,876
There's, like, one female
that runs the whole show.

1284
01:35:24,910 --> 01:35:26,810
BISHOP: Yes. The queen.

1285
01:35:26,846 --> 01:35:28,336
HUDSON: Yeah. The mama.

1286
01:35:28,381 --> 01:35:30,815
And she's badass, man.
I mean big.

1287
01:35:30,850 --> 01:35:33,410
- These things ain't ants.
- I know that.

1288
01:35:34,687 --> 01:35:37,315
Bishop, I want
these specimens destroyed...

1289
01:35:37,356 --> 01:35:39,256
as soon as
you're finished with them.

1290
01:35:39,291 --> 01:35:41,418
Mr. Burke gave instructions...

1291
01:35:41,460 --> 01:35:45,089
they were to be kept alive
for return to the Company labs.

1292
01:35:47,266 --> 01:35:50,531
He was very specific about it.

1293
01:35:50,569 --> 01:35:52,833
Those two specimens
are worth millions...

1294
01:35:52,872 --> 01:35:54,840
to the bio-weapons division.

1295
01:35:54,874 --> 01:35:58,435
If you're smart, we can both
come out of this heroes...

1296
01:35:58,477 --> 01:36:01,378
and we will be set up for life.

1297
01:36:02,548 --> 01:36:04,448
You're crazy, Burke.
Do you know that?

1298
01:36:04,483 --> 01:36:07,179
Do you think you can get
a dangerous organism...

1299
01:36:07,219 --> 01:36:08,880
past ICC quarantine?

1300
01:36:08,921 --> 01:36:12,357
How can they impound it
if they don't know about it?

1301
01:36:12,391 --> 01:36:15,417
But they will know
about it, Burke. From me.

1302
01:36:15,461 --> 01:36:17,395
Just like they'll know
you were responsible...

1303
01:36:17,430 --> 01:36:19,694
for the deaths of one hundred
fifty-seven colonists.

1304
01:36:19,732 --> 01:36:20,858
BURKE: Wait a second!

1305
01:36:20,900 --> 01:36:22,868
- You sent them to that ship.
- You're wrong.

1306
01:36:22,902 --> 01:36:24,733
I just checked
the colony log...

1307
01:36:24,770 --> 01:36:28,297
directive dated 6-12-79,
signed Burke, Carter J.

1308
01:36:28,340 --> 01:36:31,332
You sent them out there
and didn't even warn them.

1309
01:36:31,377 --> 01:36:34,346
Why didn't you warn them, Burke?

1310
01:36:34,380 --> 01:36:36,041
What if that ship
didn't even exist?

1311
01:36:36,081 --> 01:36:37,605
Did you think about that?
I didn't know.

1312
01:36:37,650 --> 01:36:40,642
So if I made a major
security situation out of it...

1313
01:36:40,686 --> 01:36:42,313
everybody steps in...

1314
01:36:42,354 --> 01:36:44,322
and there's no
exclusive rights for anybody.

1315
01:36:44,356 --> 01:36:48,315
Nobody wins. I made a decision,
and it was wrong.

1316
01:36:48,360 --> 01:36:51,124
It was a bad call, Ripley.

1317
01:36:51,163 --> 01:36:54,360
RIPLEY: Bad call?
These people are dead, Burke!

1318
01:36:54,400 --> 01:36:56,834
Haven't you any idea
what you've done?

1319
01:36:56,869 --> 01:36:59,667
I'm gonna make sure
they nail you right to the wall.

1320
01:36:59,705 --> 01:37:02,265
You're not gonna sleaze your way
out of this one.

1321
01:37:02,308 --> 01:37:03,866
Right to the wall.

1322
01:37:05,878 --> 01:37:07,106
Ripley.

1323
01:37:08,147 --> 01:37:11,446
You know,
I expected more from you.

1324
01:37:11,484 --> 01:37:14,385
I thought
you'd be smarter than this.

1325
01:37:14,420 --> 01:37:17,651
I'm happy to disappoint you.

1326
01:37:24,396 --> 01:37:26,330
[Alarm from robot sentries]

1327
01:37:31,337 --> 01:37:32,361
HUDSON: What's going on?

1328
01:37:32,404 --> 01:37:33,632
HICKS: They're coming.

1329
01:37:33,672 --> 01:37:36,368
- Where?
- In the tunnel.

1330
01:37:37,877 --> 01:37:39,139
Here we go.

1331
01:37:39,178 --> 01:37:41,806
"A" and "B" gun
tracking and firing.

1332
01:37:41,847 --> 01:37:43,337
Multiple targets.

1333
01:37:46,485 --> 01:37:49,113
[Aliens screeching
over sentry transmitter]

1334
01:37:49,154 --> 01:37:51,054
Look at those ammo counters go.

1335
01:37:53,692 --> 01:37:55,785
"B" gun's down 50 percent.

1336
01:37:56,996 --> 01:37:59,260
Man, it's a shooting gallery
down there.

1337
01:38:03,141 --> 01:38:04,938
HICKS: Sixty rounds left on "B."

1338
01:38:04,977 --> 01:38:08,208
Forty... twenty... ten.

1339
01:38:08,246 --> 01:38:10,476
"B" gun's dry. Twenty on "A."

1340
01:38:11,717 --> 01:38:13,981
Ten... five...

1341
01:38:17,823 --> 01:38:19,290
That's it.

1342
01:38:19,324 --> 01:38:22,657
HUDSON: Jesus.
They're wall-to-wall in there.

1343
01:38:24,896 --> 01:38:26,761
[Loud thumping noises]

1344
01:38:26,798 --> 01:38:28,766
They're at the pressure door.

1345
01:38:30,268 --> 01:38:32,361
Man, listen to that.

1346
01:38:32,404 --> 01:38:36,135
BISHOP: Bishop here.
I'm afraid I have some bad news.

1347
01:38:36,174 --> 01:38:38,005
Well, that's a switch.

1348
01:38:40,212 --> 01:38:43,181
RIPLEY: lt's very pretty,
but what are we looking for?

1349
01:38:43,215 --> 01:38:46,742
BISHOP: That's it.
Emergency venting.

1350
01:38:46,785 --> 01:38:51,245
HUDSON: That's beautiful, man.
That beats it all.

1351
01:38:51,289 --> 01:38:53,757
HICKS: How long till it blows?

1352
01:38:53,792 --> 01:38:55,259
BISHOP: Four hours...

1353
01:38:55,293 --> 01:38:57,761
with a blast radius
of thirty kilometers...

1354
01:38:57,796 --> 01:39:00,959
equal to about forty megatons.

1355
01:39:00,999 --> 01:39:02,296
HICKS: We got problems.

1356
01:39:02,334 --> 01:39:04,825
HUDSON: I don't fucking
believe this!

1357
01:39:04,870 --> 01:39:07,100
HICKS: Vasquez,
close the shutters.

1358
01:39:07,139 --> 01:39:09,767
RIPLEY: Why can't we
shut it down from here?

1359
01:39:09,808 --> 01:39:11,799
BISHOP: The crash
caused too much damage.

1360
01:39:11,843 --> 01:39:14,311
An overload was inevitable
at this point.

1361
01:39:14,346 --> 01:39:17,406
HUDSON:
Oh, man, I was getting short.

1362
01:39:17,449 --> 01:39:19,314
Four more weeks and out.

1363
01:39:19,351 --> 01:39:21,251
Now I'm going to buy it
on this rock.

1364
01:39:21,286 --> 01:39:22,913
VASQUEZ: Give us a break!

1365
01:39:22,954 --> 01:39:25,422
HUDSON: Four more weeks.
Oh, man.

1366
01:39:25,457 --> 01:39:28,358
RIPLEY: We need the other
drop-ship from the Sulaco.

1367
01:39:28,393 --> 01:39:31,920
Can't we bring it down
on remote?

1368
01:39:31,963 --> 01:39:35,558
The transmitter was on the APC.
It's wasted.

1369
01:39:35,600 --> 01:39:38,899
I don't care how.
We better think of a way.

1370
01:39:38,937 --> 01:39:41,804
HUDSON: Think of what?
We're fucked! We're doomed!

1371
01:39:41,840 --> 01:39:44,673
Shut up! What about
the colony transmitters?

1372
01:39:44,709 --> 01:39:46,574
The uplink tower
at the other end?

1373
01:39:46,611 --> 01:39:50,672
The hard-wiring between here
and there was damaged.

1374
01:39:50,715 --> 01:39:52,615
We can't align the dish.

1375
01:39:52,651 --> 01:39:55,051
Somebody's gonna
have to go out there...

1376
01:39:55,087 --> 01:39:58,113
take a portable terminal
and patch in manually.

1377
01:39:58,156 --> 01:40:00,886
Yeah, sure. With those things
running around?

1378
01:40:00,926 --> 01:40:03,292
You can count me out.

1379
01:40:03,328 --> 01:40:05,057
HICKS: We can count you
out of everything.

1380
01:40:05,097 --> 01:40:06,257
BISHOP: l'll go.

1381
01:40:06,298 --> 01:40:07,856
HUDSON: You go, man.

1382
01:40:07,899 --> 01:40:09,196
RIPLEY: What?

1383
01:40:09,234 --> 01:40:10,428
l'll go.

1384
01:40:10,469 --> 01:40:13,632
I'm the only one qualified
to remote-pilot the ship.

1385
01:40:13,672 --> 01:40:16,835
HUDSON: Yeah, right, man.
Bishop should go.

1386
01:40:16,875 --> 01:40:18,103
Good idea.

1387
01:40:18,143 --> 01:40:20,338
BISHOP: Believe me,
I'd prefer not to.

1388
01:40:20,378 --> 01:40:24,405
I may be synthetic,
but I'm not stupid.

1389
01:40:35,227 --> 01:40:37,024
RIPLEY: How long?

1390
01:40:37,062 --> 01:40:39,155
BISHOP: This conduit runs
almost to the uplink assembly...

1391
01:40:39,197 --> 01:40:40,596
one hundred eighty meters.

1392
01:40:40,632 --> 01:40:43,795
Say forty minutes
crawling there...

1393
01:40:43,835 --> 01:40:47,202
an hour to patch in
and align the antenna...

1394
01:40:48,840 --> 01:40:50,501
thirty minutes
to prep the ship...

1395
01:40:50,542 --> 01:40:53,010
and about fifty minutes
flight time.

1396
01:40:53,044 --> 01:40:55,535
RIPLEY: lt's gonna be close.

1397
01:40:58,049 --> 01:41:00,142
RIPLEY: Good luck.

1398
01:41:00,185 --> 01:41:01,516
BISHOP: See you soon.

1399
01:41:02,921 --> 01:41:04,752
Watch your fingers.

1400
01:41:04,789 --> 01:41:06,416
Oh.

1401
01:41:08,927 --> 01:41:11,088
VASQUEZ: Vaya con Dios, man.

1402
01:41:23,041 --> 01:41:24,975
HICKS: This is unbelievable.

1403
01:41:25,010 --> 01:41:28,309
Twenty meters and closing.
Fifteen.

1404
01:41:28,346 --> 01:41:29,745
RIPLEY: How many?

1405
01:41:29,781 --> 01:41:32,443
HICKS: Can't tell. Lots.

1406
01:41:34,019 --> 01:41:35,919
"D" gun's down 50 percent.

1407
01:41:39,257 --> 01:41:40,884
"C" gun's right behind it.

1408
01:41:44,329 --> 01:41:45,387
HUDSON: lt ain't stopping 'em.

1409
01:41:45,430 --> 01:41:47,557
Jesus, it ain't stopping 'em.

1410
01:41:47,599 --> 01:41:49,931
HICKS: A hundred and fifty
rounds on "D."

1411
01:41:49,968 --> 01:41:52,027
HUDSON: Come on, baby. Come on.

1412
01:41:52,070 --> 01:41:53,503
HICKS: One hundred rounds.

1413
01:41:55,974 --> 01:41:57,771
HUDSON: Come on, come on.

1414
01:41:57,809 --> 01:41:59,071
[Beeping]

1415
01:42:02,347 --> 01:42:04,281
"D" gun's down to twenty.

1416
01:42:05,483 --> 01:42:06,848
Ten.

1417
01:42:09,154 --> 01:42:10,644
Damn it!

1418
01:42:12,190 --> 01:42:15,216
Wait! They're retreating.

1419
01:42:19,497 --> 01:42:21,658
RIPLEY: The guns stopped them.

1420
01:42:25,337 --> 01:42:27,032
You're right.

1421
01:42:34,379 --> 01:42:36,347
HICKS: Next time
they walk right up and knock.

1422
01:42:36,381 --> 01:42:38,713
Yeah, but they don't know that.

1423
01:42:38,750 --> 01:42:41,742
They're probably looking
for other ways to get in.

1424
01:42:42,754 --> 01:42:44,187
That'll take 'em a while.

1425
01:42:44,222 --> 01:42:46,747
- Maybe we got 'em demoralized.
- Shut up.

1426
01:42:47,993 --> 01:42:50,553
I want you two
walking perimeter.

1427
01:42:52,130 --> 01:42:53,256
Move!

1428
01:43:00,772 --> 01:43:01,932
HICKS: Hey, listen.

1429
01:43:03,208 --> 01:43:05,540
We're all in strung-out shape...

1430
01:43:05,577 --> 01:43:09,604
but stay frosty and alert.

1431
01:43:10,915 --> 01:43:13,850
We can't afford to let
one of those bastards in here.

1432
01:43:13,885 --> 01:43:17,321
All right. Vámonos.

1433
01:43:25,397 --> 01:43:28,958
How long's it been
since you got any sleep?

1434
01:43:29,000 --> 01:43:30,900
Twenty-four hours?

1435
01:43:32,871 --> 01:43:36,068
Hicks, I'm not gonna end up
like those others.

1436
01:43:36,107 --> 01:43:38,974
You'll take care of it,
won't you?

1437
01:43:40,612 --> 01:43:45,072
If it comes to that,
l'll do us both.

1438
01:43:46,851 --> 01:43:51,311
Let's just make sure it doesn't
come to that, all right?

1439
01:43:51,356 --> 01:43:53,256
All right.

1440
01:43:53,291 --> 01:43:58,593
Hey, I want to introduce you
to a personal friend of mine.

1441
01:43:58,630 --> 01:44:01,929
This is an M-41A pulse-rifle,
ten millimeter...

1442
01:44:01,966 --> 01:44:06,426
with an over-and-under
30 millimeter grenade launcher.

1443
01:44:06,471 --> 01:44:08,530
Feel the weight.

1444
01:44:15,313 --> 01:44:17,781
OK, what do I do?

1445
01:44:23,121 --> 01:44:25,589
HICKS: Pull it in tight here.

1446
01:44:25,623 --> 01:44:28,285
- Right.
- Lean into it.

1447
01:44:28,326 --> 01:44:30,123
HICKS:
All right, it will kick some.

1448
01:44:31,863 --> 01:44:35,094
When the counter
reads zero here, you...

1449
01:44:35,133 --> 01:44:36,725
- I press this up?
- That's right.

1450
01:44:39,070 --> 01:44:42,198
Get another one in quick.
Slap it in hard.

1451
01:44:42,240 --> 01:44:45,004
Now you're ready
to rock 'n' roll.

1452
01:44:45,543 --> 01:44:48,478
- What's this?
- The grenade launcher.

1453
01:44:48,513 --> 01:44:51,175
I don't think you want
to mess with that.

1454
01:44:51,216 --> 01:44:55,016
You started this.
Show me everything.

1455
01:44:55,053 --> 01:44:57,044
I can handle myself.

1456
01:44:58,723 --> 01:45:00,789
Yeah, I noticed.

1457
01:45:10,565 --> 01:45:12,533
RIPLEY: How do you feel?

1458
01:45:12,567 --> 01:45:17,027
GORMAN: All right, I guess.
One hell of a hangover.

1459
01:45:17,072 --> 01:45:19,370
Look, Ripley, I just want...

1460
01:45:19,407 --> 01:45:22,399
RIPLEY: Forget it. Excuse me.

1461
01:46:14,062 --> 01:46:16,860
[Newt moaning]

1462
01:46:16,898 --> 01:46:19,025
RIPLEY: Shh, shh, shh.

1463
01:46:19,067 --> 01:46:22,400
It's OK. It's OK.

1464
01:47:32,272 --> 01:47:35,241
[Whispering]
Newt. Wake up.

1465
01:47:35,275 --> 01:47:37,743
- What?
- Be quiet.

1466
01:47:37,778 --> 01:47:39,769
We're in trouble.

1467
01:47:57,664 --> 01:48:00,258
- No!
- Aah!

1468
01:48:00,300 --> 01:48:01,631
Move, Newt!

1469
01:48:23,523 --> 01:48:24,683
RIPLEY: Hey!

1470
01:48:24,725 --> 01:48:26,454
[No sound]

1471
01:48:33,633 --> 01:48:35,828
NEWT: Help!

1472
01:48:35,869 --> 01:48:38,337
Help!

1473
01:48:38,371 --> 01:48:40,066
RIPLEY: Hicks!

1474
01:48:40,107 --> 01:48:41,665
HICKS: Say again, Bishop?

1475
01:48:41,708 --> 01:48:44,006
You've got it
into auto-refuel mode...

1476
01:48:44,044 --> 01:48:45,341
and it's sequencing right?

1477
01:48:45,378 --> 01:48:46,504
BISHOP: That's right.

1478
01:48:46,546 --> 01:48:48,605
HICKS: Good. Stay on it.

1479
01:48:48,648 --> 01:48:53,608
Get back to me when you've
activated the launch cycle.

1480
01:48:53,653 --> 01:48:55,621
He's at the uplink tower.

1481
01:48:55,655 --> 01:48:57,145
BURKE: Terrific.

1482
01:48:59,993 --> 01:49:03,952
- Hicks! Hicks!
- Help! Help!

1483
01:49:03,997 --> 01:49:05,624
Hicks! Help us!

1484
01:49:05,665 --> 01:49:07,326
Break the glass!

1485
01:49:07,367 --> 01:49:09,392
Break it, break it.

1486
01:49:09,436 --> 01:49:11,427
RIPLEY: l'll try.

1487
01:49:31,625 --> 01:49:34,651
Ripley, I'm scared.

1488
01:49:34,694 --> 01:49:36,685
Me, too.

1489
01:49:42,269 --> 01:49:43,759
Stay here.

1490
01:49:52,946 --> 01:49:55,881
[Alarm sounds]

1491
01:49:55,916 --> 01:49:59,044
HICKS: lt's the med lab.
Hudson!

1492
01:49:59,085 --> 01:50:02,543
Vasquez! Meet me in med lab.
We got a fire.

1493
01:50:02,589 --> 01:50:04,250
HUDSON: We're on our way.

1494
01:50:07,360 --> 01:50:10,557
They're coming, Newt.
Oh, please.

1495
01:50:15,769 --> 01:50:16,895
Aah!

1496
01:50:16,937 --> 01:50:18,370
Uh!

1497
01:50:24,511 --> 01:50:25,739
Aah!

1498
01:50:32,953 --> 01:50:35,444
Aah!

1499
01:50:35,488 --> 01:50:36,750
Aah!

1500
01:50:41,928 --> 01:50:43,555
Shoot it out!

1501
01:50:48,034 --> 01:50:49,934
- Hudson!
- Jesus!

1502
01:50:51,872 --> 01:50:53,464
Oh!

1503
01:50:53,506 --> 01:50:55,167
Christ, kid, look out!

1504
01:51:03,350 --> 01:51:04,783
Fucking die!

1505
01:51:15,862 --> 01:51:17,830
- Over there!
- Yeah!

1506
01:51:17,864 --> 01:51:19,855
- Ready?
- Yeah!

1507
01:51:24,371 --> 01:51:25,429
HICKS: Hudson!

1508
01:51:25,472 --> 01:51:28,032
HUDSON: Yeah, all clear.
Nailed the other one.

1509
01:51:28,074 --> 01:51:29,666
It's history, man.

1510
01:51:30,877 --> 01:51:31,969
HICKS: Jesus.

1511
01:51:33,546 --> 01:51:37,107
RIPLEY: Burke. It was Burke.

1512
01:51:38,685 --> 01:51:43,019
I say we grease this rat-fuck
son of a bitch right now.

1513
01:51:43,056 --> 01:51:45,752
HICKS: lt just doesn't make
any goddamn sense.

1514
01:51:47,861 --> 01:51:50,853
RIPLEY: He figured
that he could get an alien...

1515
01:51:50,897 --> 01:51:55,994
back through quarantine
if one of us was impregnated...

1516
01:51:56,036 --> 01:51:59,301
whatever you call it...

1517
01:51:59,339 --> 01:52:02,172
and then frozen
for the trip home.

1518
01:52:02,208 --> 01:52:06,872
Nobody would know about
the embryos we were carrying...

1519
01:52:06,913 --> 01:52:08,380
me and Newt.

1520
01:52:10,250 --> 01:52:12,241
